<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section version="5.0"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://www.docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd"
    xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mth="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
    xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xml:id="create_organisation_unit">
    <title>Create or edit an
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160518T101541+0200" comment="For SME: Who creats the original org unit hierarchy? Admin? Implmenter?" flag="done"?>organisation
        unit<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
    <para>
        <screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata width="80%" align="center"
                        fileref="resources/images/orgunits/create_new_orgunit.png" format="PNG"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </screenshot>
    </para>
    <para>You add organisation units to the hierarchy one by one, either as a
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160518T102014+0200" comment="For SME: Can you crate a new root? 
Follow-up with SME before release.
- 2.24. you can only have one root unit." flag="done"?>root
        unit<?oxy_comment_end?> or as a child of a selected organisation unit. You can only have one
        root unit.</para>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                    role="bold">Organisation unit</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Organisation
                    unit</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click the add button.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select which organisation unit your new organisation unit will belong to:</para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Parent organisation unit</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>In the organisation unit tree, locate the parent organisation unit and
                        select it. Your selection is marked in yellow.</para>
                    <tip>
                        <para>Click the arrows to expand the organisation unit
                            t<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161205T104317+0100" comment="Cecilia 5 Dec 2016: No search for 2.25 or master.
Removed text:
&quot; or by searching for it by name or code&quot;
and note:
&quot;The search is case-insensitive for organisation unit names. For codes you need to type the exact code.&quot;" flag="done"?>ree<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
                    </tip>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Select</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Enter a <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis> of the organisation unit.</para>
            <para>Each organisation unit must have an unique name.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Enter a <emphasis role="bold">Short name</emphasis> for the organisation
                unit.</para>
            <para>Typically, the short name is an abbreviation of the full organisation unit name.
                This attribute is often used in reports to display the name of the organisation
                unit, where space is limited.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) Assign a <emphasis role="bold">Code</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>In many countries organisation units are assigned a code.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) Type a <emphasis role="bold">Description</emphasis> of the organisation
                unit.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select an <emphasis role="bold">Opening date</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>The opening dates control which organisation units that existed at a point in
                time, for example when analysing historical data.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>If applicable, select a <emphasis role="bold">Closed date</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Comment</emphasis> field, enter any additional
                information that you would like to add.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) In the <emphasis role="bold">URL</emphasis> field, enter a link to an
                external web site that has additional information about the organisation
                unit.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Enter contact information:</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Contact person</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Address</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>E-mail</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Phone number</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161205T113400+0100" comment="WHen x-refs work, add link to GIS section" flag="done"?>Optional<?oxy_comment_end?>)
                Enter <emphasis role="bold">Latitude</emphasis> and <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Longitude</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>You must have latitude and longitude values to create maps in the <emphasis
                    role="bold">GIS</emphasis> app. Then your organisation units can be represented
                as points on a map, for example a health facility. Without this information, the
                    <emphasis role="bold">GIS</emphasis> app will not work. </para>
            <para>It might be more efficient to import coordinates later as a batch job for all
                organisation units using the <emphasis role="bold">Import-Export</emphasis> app. You
                also use the <emphasis role="bold">Import-Export</emphasis> app to create polygons.
                A polygon is an organisation unit that represent an administrative boundary.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>If applicable, select <emphasis role="bold"
                    >D<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161205T120303+0100" comment="When x-refs work, add link to Data set section" flag="done"?>ata
                    sets<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis> and assign
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161205T120116+0100" comment="What is the purpose of having them here?
A user can only register data for a data set if that data set is assigned to the same org unit as the user." flag="done"?>them<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
            <note>
                <para>You control whether a user should be able to assign data sets to an
                    organisation unit in the <emphasis role="bold">System Settings</emphasis>
                    app:</para>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">System Settings</emphasis> app, click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Access</emphasis> and select <emphasis role="bold">Allow
                        assigning object to related objects during add or update</emphasis>.</para>
            </note>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>If applicable, enter custom attributes values, for example <emphasis role="bold"
                    >HR identifier</emphasis>.</para>
            <note>
                <para>You configure the custom attributes in the <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Maintenance</emphasis> app:</para>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Other</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Attribute</emphasis><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160518T114951+0200" comment="At next revsision, add x-ref here." flag="done"?>. </para>
                <?oxy_comment_end?>
            </note>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
</section>
